summaries.short: Shoshanna thrives and flirts in Japan; Hannah finds something unexpected on Fran's phone; Jessa assesses Adam's character.
summaries.full: Thriving at her new job in Japan, Shoshanna finds herself flirting with her boss, but reminds her work friends that she has a 'kind of' boyfriend back in America. Hannah makes a shocking discovery on Fran's phone and struggles with how to react. After viewing Adam's performance on a TV police procedural, Jessa shares her insights into his character.

summaries.short: Hannah helps out her dad; Adam and Jessa spend a day together; Ray fumes about a competing coffee shop; Elijah makes a connection.
summaries.full: In NYC, an erratic roommate leads Fran to move in with Hannah. Later, Hannah gets an urgent call from her dad, who is trying to navigate a new type of dating. After a run-in at an AA meeting, Adam and Jessa spend the day together. Ray fumes over the new cafe across the street, which he fears is hurting his business. Elijah is hit on by a famous news anchor.

summaries.full: Hannah and her mom embark on a female-empowerment retreat, where Loreen hopes for clarity on her situation with Tad, and Hannah relishes some time away from Fran. summaries.short: Season Five Premiere. At Marnie's wedding, Hannah brings Fran along as her date; Shoshanna is tasked with carrying out Marnie's wishes.
summaries.full: Season Five Premiere. Marnie micromanages her upstate wedding to Desi while trying to maintain the facade of the breezy bride, tasking Shoshanna with kicking out Fran, Hannah's date, so the girls can get ready. Banished to the boys' den, Fran has an awkward moment with Adam; and a dejected Ray steps in to help a nervous Desi with his wedding-day jitters.
